A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 6 of Chapter 1 of Title 37 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to the Behavioral Health Reform and Innovation Commission, so as to revise the
3 subcommittees; to extend the automatic repeal date; to provide for related matters; to provide
4 for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 6 of Chapter 1 of Title 37 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
8 Behavioral Health Reform and Innovation Commission, is amended by revising Code
9 Section 37-1-115, relating to subcommittees, as follows:
10 "37-1-115.
11 (a) Except as otherwise provided in this Code section, the The chairperson of the
12 commission shall appoint members of the following subcommittees from among the
13 membership of the commission and may also appoint up to two other
14 noncommission-member persons as he or she may determine to be necessary as relevant
15 to and consistent with this article:
16 (1) Children and Adolescent Behavioral Health;
